Description: GTK/OpenGL editor and viewer for atomistic structures
 gdislinux is a desktop application for building, visualizing, and analyzing
 atomistic and crystallographic structures.
 .
 This package is the Debian/Ubuntu continuation path for the former gdis
 package, rebuilt around the renewed GTK4 backend instead of the obsolete GTK2
 and gtkglext stack that led to removal from Debian unstable. The GTK4 port is
 still a modernization branch, but it already restores practical molecule
 rendering, selection overlays, diffraction graphs, and iso-surface workflows.
 .
 The packaged launcher is installed as /usr/bin/gdislinux.

Package: gdislinux-qbox
Architecture: any
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
 ${shlibs:Depends},
 python3,
 python3-numpy
Recommends:
 gdislinux-qbox-data,
 openmpi-bin
Description: Qbox engine bundle for gdislinux
 gdislinux-qbox installs the Qbox executable and helper scripts used by the
 gdislinux GTK4 continuation package.
 .
 The package places the Qbox engine at /usr/lib/gdislinux/qbox so gdislinux
 can auto-detect it without manual setup. It also installs the
 gdislinux-qbox wrapper command and the qbox-out-to-xyz.sh conversion helper.

Package: gdislinux-qbox-data
Architecture: all
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends}
Enhances:
 gdislinux,
 gdislinux-qbox
Description: Qbox demo data bundle for gdislinux
 gdislinux-qbox-data ships packaged XML pseudopotentials plus curated Qbox
 sample files for the gdislinux Qbox dialog.
 .
 The demo XML files are installed under /usr/share/gdislinux/qbox/potentials
 and the included example files are installed under
 /usr/share/gdislinux/qbox/examples.
